						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I seem to remember that one of the Double Dragon games uses another solution: horizontal mirroring, and whenever the camera starts to move into the status bar, move the status bar to the other nametable. With a semi-unrolled loop, it should be possible to push up to 4 rows of status bar to VRAM plus the corresponding attributes during one NTSC vblank.</div>
<br />Yes, this is a valid solution that we don't talk about much (I didn't even know it was used in Double Dragon). The fact that you'd have to give up the regular PPU updates for a frame just to reposition the status bar makes this option less interesting IMO, but you could probably make a more dynamic system that progressively draws one status bar as the vertical scrolling changes (i.e. the closer the screen gets to one status bar the more of the other is drawn).</div>

